The paper deals with hypothesis testing for arbitrary unknown distributions, which is a problem that falls under the purview of information theory (cs.IT). The use of nonparametric methods and distributional distance metrics suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.ST). The asymptotic analysis of the problem and the consideration of countably infinite variations within a family of distributions may also make it relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
